-- Astra Agro Sells 4,000 Tons of Palm Oil at Auction
-- B y   F e m i   A d i
-- 2012-03-12T11:41:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-12/astra-agro-sells-4-000-tons-of-palm-oil-at-auction-table-.html
PT Astra Agro Lestari ,  Indonesia ’s
biggest listed plantation company by market value, accepted bids
for 4,000 metrics tons of the 9,000 tons of  palm oil  it offered
at an auction in Jakarta today.  Separately,  PT Kharisma Pemasaran Bersama Nusantara , which
sells palm oil from Indonesia’s state-owned plantations, failed
to sell 10,000 ton of palm oil at an auction in Jakarta today.  The following table lists the results of the sale, based on
a faxed statement. The volumes are given in metric tons, while
prices are in rupiah per kilogram unless stated otherwise.  Indonesia is the world’s largest producer of palm oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
